Mostly system fix. East could be slightly faulted for the initial
response. As the auction shows, 1H didn't really provide any extra
options over 1D. An initial jump shift looks good too. I hope those
who like 2NT-then-4NT showing 18-19 will agree this hand is too
strong.

West could rebid 3C but only in hindsight. 1NT seems reasonable.

As the auction went East can see a possible grand slam even without
West's long suit but I would also just bid 6NT. West can see that if
East has 17 points including K, K, KQ, KQ, and no 5-card suit, then
7NT is 5/6 to make (2 right jacks, 50% if the wrong jack). However, if
East is missing any of those 6 good cards, the grand slam rates to be
below par. Conclusion: 5NT (forcing, inviting 7) is pointless as
insufficiently delicate. 3C or 3D are far too delicate.

Charles
