East was guilty of lazy bidding. 7NT will be excellent opposite a less
than minimum 1NT rebid such as: xx, Kxx, KQx, KQJxx. However, this is
the type of hand where good methods and experience in slam bidding are
needed, in a casual partnership, East could not be faulted for taking
the simple auction.

Suggested auction:
1C  -  1H
1NT -  2D
3C  -  4C
5C  -  5NT
7C  -  pass

2D = GF checkback
3C = 5+ card club suit
4C = GF slam try
5C = denying an ace
5NT = trying again for a grand
7C = I must have whatever partner needs

converting to 7NT would be reasonable, but on the offchance partner
needs a spade ruff, 7C is a safer.

Andrew
