I was think about a previous post where the last bid was 5NT.
The 5NT bid simply asks partner to bid seven if he has a maximum but
if you bid a grand with a minimum but with playing strength you risk
going to seven missing an ace.

Sure bidding 4C and then 5C is another way to approach the hand.
Certainly, it is better than bidding 6NT.
However, you are still guessing. To say opener with all four kings and
a maximum hand can't bid 7NT seems to be asking a lot since partner
could have a different hands where you just make 7NT on sheer brute
power. The fact that you can miss some lay down grands with a 4C-5C
sequence means you are not covered in all cases. Again you are
guessing.

Basically, the decision to open 1C and rebid 1NT instead of 2C created
a situation where a grand that should have been trivially bid without
guessing was not bid and even if you decided to make a grand slam
invite after a 1NT rebid it is not entirely risk free.

Eric Leong

