I would not bid 6NT with your hand immediately for the reason that
bidding the field 6NT is only going to get you at best average. The
only way you are going to win match points on the bidding is to find a
good excuse to be in a grand or a strong excuse to stay out of slam.
So you have every incentive to slow things down and explore if
alternative contracts to 6NT are reasonable.

On the given hands, if the deal was in the first day qualifying
session of a US national pairs event, I would suspect 7NT would be
worth about 75% board.  7C would be worth about a 37% board, and 6NT
would be worth about a 13% board and I am probably being a little
generous to the pairs who didn't get to 7NT.

